# Presentation Layer Rules

## No hardcoded texts
Every string shown in the UI must be localized via `context.l10n`. Add the key to **all** `.arb` files under `lib/src/core/language/l10n/`.

```dart
// ❌ BAD — current violations in user_config_example_screen.dart
Text('Snackbar')
Text('Banner')
BaseSnackbar.success(context, message: 'Route saved successfully')
BaseSnackbar.error(context, message: 'Failed to load route data')

// ✅ GOOD
Text(context.l10n.snackbarSectionTitle)
Text(context.l10n.bannerSectionTitle)
BaseSnackbar.success(context, message: context.l10n.routeSavedSuccessfully)
BaseSnackbar.error(context, message: context.l10n.failedToLoadRouteData)
```

New keys go in every `.arb` file:
```json
// app_en.arb
"snackbarSectionTitle": "Snackbar",
"routeSavedSuccessfully": "Route saved successfully"
```

## No force unwrap without null check

Never use `!` to force-unwrap a nullable value without first checking it with `if` or a null-aware operator.

```dart
// ❌ BAD — crashes if null despite listenWhen guard
final failure = state.failure!;

// ✅ GOOD — explicit null check before use
final failure = state.failure;
if (failure == null) return;

// ✅ GOOD — null-aware access when a fallback exists
final message = state.failure?.message ?? context.l10n.defaultErrorMessage;
```

## No hardcoded colors
- ❌ `Color(0xFF123456)`, `Colors.red`, `Colors.green.shade400`
- ✅ `context.colorScheme.error`, `context.colorScheme.primary`

## Context extensions
Never call `Theme.of(context)`, `ColorScheme.of(context)`, or `AppLocalizations.of(context)` directly — use `context.colorScheme`, `context.l10n`, etc. See `core.mdc` for the full property table.

## Input fields — no TextEditingController
Input state lives in BLoC via `FieldState`. Read value from state, dispatch events on change, show `FieldState.error` when invalid.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — hypothetical user_config display name field
BlocBuilder<UserConfigEditBloc, UserConfigEditState>(
  builder: (context, state) => TextField(
    onChanged: (v) => context.read<UserConfigEditBloc>().add(UserConfigDisplayNameChanged(v)),
    decoration: InputDecoration(
      labelText: context.l10n.displayName,
      errorText: state.displayName.isInvalid ? state.displayName.error : null,
    ),
  ),
)

// ❌ BAD
final _nameController = TextEditingController();
TextField(controller: _nameController)
```

## Failure display, buttons, dialogs and bottom sheets
See `presentation-components.mdc` for the full `FailureType` switch example, button catalogue (`BaseFilledButton`, `BaseElevatedButton`, etc.), `BaseDialog`, and `BaseBottomSheet` usage.

## Imports
- ❌ NO imports from any `data/` layer
- ❌ NO imports from another feature's `presentation/` or BLoC directly — rely on DI

## File naming
Files must be prefixed with the feature name. Screens use `_screen.dart` suffix, never `_page.dart`.
- ✅ `user_config_example_screen.dart`, `user_config_theme_dropdown.dart`
- ❌ `example_screen.dart`, `theme_dropdown.dart`, `user_config_example_page.dart`


- one widget,screen one file. Never keep two classes into the one file
